                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18260914-242-off1386 t18260914-242-crimeloc1388"></join> - I saw the prisoner, and another lad, at a distance from him - there were two gentlemen before them, and I saw the prisoner take this handkerchief from a gentleman's pocket, who gave his name as Rowland Ingram, but begged not to be bound over to prosecute, as he was going into the country - as soon as the prisoner had taken it, I ran over and took him with it in his hand.</p>
